&lt;p&gt;As an Electrical I&amp;amp;C Engineer, you will design, document, and implement ground-up electrical power, instrumentation, and control systems for both a new industrial enrichment&amp;nbsp;facility and a range of advanced prototypes and R&amp;amp;D systems.&amp;nbsp;This role spans control panel design, PLC-based automation, instrumentation, and hands-on system&amp;nbsp;integration, with scope and responsibility determined by experience level. You will work across early R&amp;amp;D&amp;nbsp;prototypes through full facility-scale systems, engaging directly with hardware throughout the lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open to multiple levels of experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and test ground-up electrical and controls systems for new facilities, advanced prototypes, and R&amp;amp;D systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, test, and integrate instrumentation and controls systems for industrial automation applications, including:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Control panel schematics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wiring diagrams and I/O documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Panel layouts and harness documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use electrical CAD tools to produce and maintain detailed drawings.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and support PLC-based controls systems, including instrumentation, field devices, and control architectures.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and analyze AC power systems for industrial equipment and control panels, including single-phase and three-phase power distribution.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support design and integration of facility electrical infrastructure systems such as UPS systems, battery backup systems, generators, and backup power distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate electrical, mechanical, process, and software systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop technical documentation and specifications for internal use, vendors, and contractors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support testing, commissioning, and ongoing system improvements across R&amp;amp;D and facility deployments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
